text.__SUMMARY__: Odostomia engbergi is a species of sea snail, a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Pyramidellidae, the pyrams and their allies.This species was named for Dr. Carl C. Engberg.
text.Distribution: This marine species occurs in the Pacific Ocean off San Juan Island, Puget Sound, State of Washington, USA.
